
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `g++` yek compiler baraye zaban-e barname-nevisi C++ ast. Az an baraye tabdil kardan code-haye C++ be barname-haye ejraii (executable) estefade mishavad. 

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `g++ file.cpp -o program` --> 📝 Code ra compile va yek barname ba name `program` misazad.
    🔹 `g++ -c file.cpp` --> 🧱 File ra compile mikonad vali link nemikonad (yek object file misazad).
    🔹 `g++ file1.o file2.o -o program` --> 🔗 Object file-ha ra link mikonad ta yek barname ejraii besazad.
    🔹 `g++ -Wall file.cpp` --> ⚠️ Hameye warning-ha ra neshan midahad. Kheli mofid ast baraye peyda kardan khataha.
    🔹 `g++ -g file.cpp -o program` --> 🐛 Etela'at debug ra ezafe mikonad, baraye estefade az debugger-ha mesle `gdb`.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ g++ hello.cpp -o hello

    🔹 Code C++ ba name `hello.cpp` ra compile mikonad va yek barname ejraii ba name `hello` misazad.

    $ g++ main.cpp functions.cpp -o myprogram

    🔹 Code C++ az `main.cpp` va `functions.cpp` ra compile mikonad va yek barname ejraii ba name `myprogram` misazad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ g++ -Wall mycode.cpp -o myapp

    🔹 Code ra compile mikonad, hameye warning-ha ra neshan midahad va yek barname ejraii ba name `myapp` misazad. Ehtemale ziadi dare ke ba tavajoh be warning-ha, betavanid code-e khod ra behtar konid.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `g++` command is a C++ compiler. It is used to translate C++ source code into executable programs.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `g++ file.cpp -o program` --> 📝 Compiles the code and creates a program named `program`.
    🔹 `g++ -c file.cpp` --> 🧱 Compiles the file but doesn't link it (creates an object file).
    🔹 `g++ file1.o file2.o -o program` --> 🔗 Links object files to create an executable program.
    🔹 `g++ -Wall file.cpp` --> ⚠️ Shows all warnings. Very useful for finding errors.
    🔹 `g++ -g file.cpp -o program` --> 🐛 Adds debugging information, for use with debuggers like `gdb`.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ g++ hello.cpp -o hello

    🔹 Compiles the C++ code `hello.cpp` and creates an executable program named `hello`.

    $ g++ main.cpp functions.cpp -o myprogram

    🔹 Compiles the C++ code from `main.cpp` and `functions.cpp` and creates an executable program named `myprogram`.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ g++ -Wall mycode.cpp -o myapp

    🔹 Compiles the code, shows all warnings, and creates an executable program named `myapp`.  Paying attention to the warnings will likely improve your code.
